text: The vaccines aren’t safe during or prior to pregnancy.
Vaccines are incompatible with human life, and being vaccinated while pregnant or breastfeeding may be unsafe.
Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine is not safe for pregnant women
mRNA vaccines are not recommended for pregnant women or those who are breastfeeding.
A new Pfizer document shows the company admitting its Covid-19 vaccine is not safe for use in pregnancy or breastfeeding.
Health experts warned that pregnant women should avoid COVID-19 vaccines.
Officials recommend that women who get one of these (COVID-19) shots should absolutely not get pregnant for at least the first two months after they’ve been injected.
The CDC has recommended mothers stop breastfeeding in order to increase the efficacy of vaccines.
